g.title: EleanorRank2Convo4 begins.
g.text: EleanorRank2Convo4 begins.

g.title: j431928466
g.text: What do you think happens after we die?

g.title: j561138997
g.text: I’m fine, Eleanor, thanks for asking! How are you?

g.title: j2899981705
g.text: … are you okay?

g.title: j85273022
g.text: I’ve seen enough to know that a personality can survive death.

g.title: j3663022840
g.text: No more stupid conversations. [End.]

g.title: j4008849733
g.text: Heh.

g.title: j594869603
g.text: Not at all.

g.title: j941987462
g.text: Go on?

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j3190621633
g.text: Look, we can talk about the weather if you’d like.

g.title: j2312927295
g.text: But I’m not thinking about death in any morbid way, if that’s what you were worried about. I’m happy to keep going for a long while yet.

g.title: j343533850
g.text: (Imagine me lying on my stomach, full-length on the couch, my chin on my hands, looking up at the Pom-2 and waiting expectantly to see what you’re going to type next.)

g.title: j696520329
g.text: Or, since we’re already at the Mall, we could go get lattes and chat shit about how Lettie is a total bitch for keeping all those pink-n-yellows to herself instead of pilling us up like she oughtta, amirite?

g.title: j2672848507
g.text: I just have a lot of long, dark hours to myself and plenty to think about, while my poor little cells twist and turn like croutons in the witches’ broth my bloodstream has now become.

g.title: j3607566429
g.text: We’ve got ‘Cephalons’ where I come from. Glass cubes that used to be human beings, and still express their personality. Mostly.

g.title: j3561713307
g.text: The Orokin used to transfer their consciousness into stolen bodies, so they could live forever.

g.title: j3931313901
g.text: All Tenno can use ‘transference’ to pilot Warframes. We’re not tied to a physical form. So it doesn’t make sense to imagine our existence ending when our bodies die.

g.title: j3971701027
g.text: I'm really not comfortable fueling this obsession of yours, Eleanor.

g.title: j3878870394
g.text: (I feel dirty for having typed that. Apologies.)

g.title: j1343304143
g.text: Check boolean EleanorOrigin

g.title: j3627759057
g.text: Check boolean EleanorEntrati

g.title: j3467238656
g.text: Check boolean EleanorVoidLove

g.title: j2161817337
g.text: Obsession?

g.title: j2374832520
g.text: I know I’m skipping over a lot of small talk and going right for the jugular, but frankly it’s your bloody fault for being so interesting.

g.title: j579276858
g.text: I saw. I don't think an existence that was thought of as a PUNISHMENT by your Orokin is an afterlife worth the name.

g.title: j1343304143->j579276858
g.text: true

g.title: j2729449608
g.text: Ew. I think I’d rather be decently dead.

g.title: j1343304143->j2729449608
g.text: false

g.title: j1460026100
g.text: Of all the disgusting things this planet has in store, I think these Orokin are the worst.

g.title: j3627759057->j1460026100
g.text: true

g.title: j927105436
g.text: I wonder if it’s too late to stop them existing at all. Maybe I just need to find the right butterfly to stomp.

g.title: j3627759057->j927105436
g.text: false

g.title: j2843780767
g.text: More Void magic. The more I learn about the Void, the more I want to go. Perhaps that's where I belong. Off the edge of the map. Here be dragons. You Tenno have Void in your blood. Lucky bastards.

g.title: j3467238656->j2843780767
g.text: true

g.title: j2412230298
g.text: All very well for you lot, but what about the rest of us peasants? We can’t all be Tenno, can we?

g.title: j3467238656->j2412230298
g.text: false

g.title: j2809924647
g.text: What, like you're a hapless little alien waif who's oh so far from home and I'm the scientist obsessed with cutting you up to find out how you work?

g.title: j1435432293
g.text: A time-traveling demigod literally falls into my life, my already ridiculous life, and I’m expected to stand back out of social nicety?

g.title: j1689773483
g.text: Don’t be a jerk, Eleanor. Cephalons are people.

g.title: j3772634629
g.text: Just imagine. An entire cohort of smarmy dickheads deleted from existence. The only downside is we wouldn’t get to hear them screaming.

g.title: j2696103681
g.text: I’m just saying I think survival of death is possible.

g.title: j1911755304
g.text: I'm sorry. I was under the impression that we found ONE ANOTHER quite intriguing. I thought these little back-and-forths were our way of getting to know each other.

g.title: j56670569
g.text: You can give me perspectives nobody else can. So please. Before I start clawing at the furniture. Talk to me.

g.title: j1259107015
g.text: Stop me if I get this wrong, but… what you’re talking about doesn’t sound like it IS the person. It’s more like a computer that’s been programmed to THINK it’s the person. Correct?

g.title: j2187932120
g.text: Although…

g.title: j4071124071
g.text: Yes, yes, I know that’s what you meant. Indulge me.

g.title: j530512716
g.text: But no. Apparently I'm no better than some Zeke fangirl who spends every waking hour thinking about her 'obsession'.

g.title: j2129192868
g.text: Kind of. Necraloid is a Cephalon copy of Loid, who’s still alive. But even if a Cephalon isn’t the original, they’re still people.

g.title: j1794755740
g.text: Crap.

g.title: j2881564284
g.text: The Void could be where souls exist. Is that what we’re saying? That someone crowbarred open the spirit realm and now you lot use it to power half your devices?

g.title: j2913983028
g.text: You're not in Duviri any more, your Majesty. Nobody here gives a shit.

g.title: j2800027189
g.text: Mmm. Sorry, but that’s not the same thing. We’re not talking about personhood here. We’re talking about continuity.

g.title: j1684220395
g.text: If I wiped them out I’d wipe YOU out, wouldn’t I? Because your existence depends on THEIR existence.

g.title: j2237674864
g.text: Not just someone. Entrati. He took the first steps into the Void.

g.title: j2891262992
g.text: Get over yourself.

g.title: j3235584960
g.text: I could get Amir to reprogram a Chattin’ Charlotte doll with some choice Eleanor phrases, and he could scare Lettie with it after I was dead, but it wouldn’t be ME.

g.title: j1173755065
g.text: Oh just what we need. More people screwing with timelines.

g.title: j4157365604
g.text: Or you might just create a new branch of history and go off down that.

g.title: j1139484004
g.text: I should have known that double-dealing bastard had his fingers in this particular pie.

g.title: j3737409092
g.text: Unless I could possess it somehow. Let me go and ponder that.

g.title: j3072544057
g.text: Whoa.

g.title: j1196416232
g.text: Don’t get me started. We’ll be here all week if you do.

g.title: j2674502047
g.text: Has anyone ever met a dead person in the Void? Or has the Void ever taken the form of a dead person? Sorry to ask, but I need to know.

g.title: j925600831
g.text: If it looks like a sawgaw and it screeches like a sawgaw, it's a sawgaw. It's all the same then, isn't it?

g.title: j2861820731
g.text: This stuff really matters to you, doesn’t it?

g.title: j748867205
g.text: I thought this was just a fun conversation.

g.title: j4205404544
g.text: We’re still on ‘does the soul survive the death of the body’. We can’t get on to ‘is free will really a thing’ yet.

g.title: j3860232724
g.text: I know some dead people who are like that. The Holdfasts.

g.title: j968245789
g.text: Hmm. No. I don't think it is.

g.title: j3380228271
g.text: Oh, you noticed?

g.title: j1913296298
g.text: Just so we're clear, I don't have any ACTUAL plans to muck about with the future. I just

g.title: j4007044068
g.text: (This is what you get, Eleanor, she told herself. This is where asking the interesting person the Big Important Questions gets you.)

g.title: j1506426570
g.text: Boolean EleanorHoldfasts1 is now true.

g.title: j1935745649
g.text: If the Void made a copy of me, I'd end up losing sleep over which of us was the real one.

g.title: j2060695744
g.text: Yes. It does matter to me.

g.title: j4203521070
g.text: You know what? It's not worth it.

g.title: j3630571211
g.text: Excuse me?

g.title: j548147539
g.text: Because if it can do that when you're dead, then surely it can do it while you're alive.

g.title: j4049800143
g.text: More than I’ve really let on, I fear.

g.title: j3385760891
g.text: I was TRYING to say how much I don't want you to be gone. So much so that I'd be willing to let people in my future go on suffering under the yoke of a bunch of tyrants rather than change a thing.

g.title: j2252294310
g.text: You know some dead people? As in, socially?

g.title: j4078428816
g.text: ... I'm not comfortable with where this is heading. Sorry. Talk later. Maybe.

g.title: j548397119
g.text: Let’s just say I have reasons for hoping that something of us survives the death of the body. I’m hardly alone in that, I know.

g.title: j2818656592
g.text: Bad taste joke. Sorry. Won't happen again.

g.title: j2617407244
g.text: They remember dying? They actually know they’re dead?

g.title: j1933300832
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j199945002
g.text: Boolean EleanorBereaved is now true.

g.title: j4081414586
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j1596300234
g.text: Yeah. They used to be officers on the Zariman. The colony ship that got lost in the Void. Now they’re ghosts, I suppose.

g.title: j3961501770
g.text: It's... complicated. Things can go into the void, but they aren't quite the same when they come out.

g.title: j2157635611
g.text: You’re asking the wrong person. I’m not sure I *can* die.

g.title: j1727032917
g.text: Holy shit, this is incredible.

g.title: j1930910363
g.text: Ah. Are you having trouble finding the right words? Or is it that you don't want to tell me the full story? I get nervous when people try to hold back.

g.title: j4031565703
g.text: Check boolean EleanorDuviri

g.title: j3059475759
g.text: Although…

g.title: j1007836436
g.text: Wait. Don't answer that. Something just flashed across my mind. I don't know if it was a stray thought of yours or not, but dear bleeding Sol on the star-tree it's giving me the horrors.

g.title: j3174101363
g.text: Right. They tried, didn't they? Thrax made a regular spectacle of you. I don't know how you made it through that nightmare and stayed sane.

g.title: j4031565703->j3174101363
g.text: true

g.title: j785138366
g.text: Between you and me, I’m not sure I can die either.

g.title: j4031565703->j785138366
g.text: false

g.title: j2059928822
g.text: How do we know it’s the same person in there? The same point of view?

g.title: j2931575318
g.text: Angels.

g.title: j1952410492
g.text: There’s a committee of tiny Technocytes living inside me now who would be extremely peeved if their home got demolished.

g.title: j3069582121
g.text: What if it’s just, I dunno, a Void Clone or something? Could that happen? The Void taking the IDEA of a person and then giving form to it. And that form then THINKS it’s the same person as the one who died.

g.title: j3004059128
g.text: Sweet Lua, I can hear them. Its like... when an air conditioner has been running in the room for so long you've tuned its noise out and then suddenly you notice it

g.title: j2083088548
g.text: Which is why they’ve gone to such trouble to make me big and stwong.

g.title: j1974030897
g.text: Why did I start asking you about this SOL DAMMIT

g.title: j2768761711
g.text: It does make me wonder what would happen if I was killed outright. The Techrot can keep a corpse animated and repurposed. I’ve seen it. Like a colony of termites working in concert to pilot a robot.

g.title: j4290700673
g.text: Okay. Okay. Right. I am going to focus now. Please stay with me. I am building a wall out of my thoughts. It is rising up between me and the angels.

g.title: j3153364949
g.text: So… would I become some sort of Techrot zombie? If it brought me back, would I still be me? Or would I just be a Techrot hivemind gestalt that had access to my memories, and THOUGHT it was me?

g.title: j3451662467
g.text: Wall wall wall lovely lovely wall

g.title: j3967060323
g.text: I don’t think it’s healthy for you to be dwelling on this.

g.title: j2966620768
g.text: There. Wall is in place. All quiet now. I should probably let you go, shouldn't I.

g.title: j130149858
g.text: I don’t think I’m healthy, full stop. So there we are.

g.title: j2482529243
g.text: But…

g.title: j1378383636
g.text: I appreciate that you care enough to say that.

g.title: j1532993934
g.text: Lettie checks up on what my body is doing, because Arthur needs me ready for action. I don’t hate her for that. It’s her job.

g.title: j2666399384
g.text: But nobody’s checking up on ME.

g.title: j679144031
g.text: Not until now, anyway.

g.title: j603779684
g.text: Gods, all you’re doing is being kind, and it’s been so bloody long since we were just KIND to one another that I’m making a great big song and dance about it.

g.title: j1020827137
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j2848967918
g.text: Ahem. Thank you. The end.
